Executive pay that “got out of
line” and a lack of women on corporate boards are some of the
U.K.’s “key failings,” the Financial Times said, citing for
the Institute of Directors Director-General Simon Walker.  Things “could get worse before they get better” in 2012,
the FT cited Walker as saying in a New Year’s message.  To contact the reporter on this story:
